#     CROSS-DOMAIN convergence (same integer in independent fields),
#     NOT on per-match significance. Abstracts are explicit about this
#     and the shard preserves the framing without upgrading.
#   - Engineering papers conflate three categories:
#     (a) mathematical theorems (non-falsifiable),
#     (b) empirical convergence (engineers chose, not theory),
#     (c) speculative predictions.
#     This shard tags each entry with the category per source.
